                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d930">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Adee</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Eddy</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1901-10-03">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 3, 1901</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>(Mr. Adee directs Mr. Eddy to informally consult the Russian ambassador and say
                    that the United States Government would be pleased if he might feel free to use
                    at once his good offices and exert his influence, in whatever direction, in aid
                    of the rescue of Miss Stone, and states that Mr. Eddy may, in the same way,
                    invoke the aid of any other foreign minister who may be able to render
                    assistance.)</p>
            </div>
        </body>
